"Hermippus, in his Sale of Diogenes, says that he was taken prisoner and put up to be sold, and asked what he could do;
and he answered, " Govern men."
And so he bade the crier " give notice that if any one wants to purchase a master, there is one here for him."
When he was ordered not to sit down ;
