On one occasion he saw the son of a courtesan throwing a stone at a crowd, and said to him, "Take care, lest you hit your father."
When a boy showed him a sword that he had received from one to whom he had done some discreditable service, he told him, " The sword is a good sword, but the handle is infamous."
And when some people were praising a man who had given him some- thing, he said to them, " And do not you praise me who was worthy to receive it?"
